data.chText: 命中注定的事（尤指坏事）；命运的安排
data.enText: the things, especially bad things, that will happen or have happened to sb/sth

data.chText: 这三个人命运未卜。
data.enText: The fate of the three men is unknown.

data.chText: 她坐在外面，等待命运对她作出的安排。
data.enText: She sat outside, waiting to find out her fate.

data.chText: 法庭将决定我们的命运。
data.enText: The court will decide our fate/fates .

data.chText: 每一个经理命运都是如此。
data.enText: Each of the managers suffered the same fate .

data.chText: 政府抛弃了难民，让他们听天由命。
data.enText: The government had abandoned the refugees to their fate .

data.chText: 从那时起我们的命运就已经注定了。
data.enText: From that moment our fate was sealed (= our future was decided) .

data.chText: 命运；天数；定数；天意
data.enText: the power that is believed to control everything that happens and that cannot be stopped or changed

data.chText: 那天我很幸运。
data.enText: Fate was kind to me that day.

data.chText: 由于命运的奇特安排，我和安迪乘坐了同一架飞机。
data.enText: By a strange twist of fate , Andy and I were on the same plane.
a fate worse than death

data.chText: （可能发生的）极可怕的事
data.enText: a terrible thing that could happen
tempt fate/providence

data.chText: 玩命；冒险；鲁莽
data.enText: to do sth too confidently in a way that might mean that your good luck will come to an end

data.text: luck ♦ chance ♦ coincidence ♦ accident ♦ fortune ♦ fate ♦ destiny ♦ providence

data.chText: 以上各词均指机遇、命运、运气。
data.enText: These are all words for things that happen or the force that causes them to happen.
luck

data.chText: 指机遇、命运、运气：
data.enText: the force that causes good or bad things to happen to people

data.chText: 这戒指总是给我带来好运。
data.enText: This ring has always brought me good luck.
chance

data.chText: 指偶然、碰巧、意外：
data.enText: the way that some things happen without any cause that you can see or understand

data.chText: 这结果可能纯属意外。
data.enText: The results could simply be due to chance.
coincidence

data.chText: 指出人意料的巧合、巧事：
data.enText: the fact of two things happening at the same time by chance, in a surprising way

data.chText: 他们因一连串奇妙的巧合而相遇。
data.enText: They met through a series of strange coincidences.
accident

data.chText: 指意外、偶然的事：
data.enText: something that happens unexpectedly and is not planned in advance

data.chText: 他们早到仅仅是偶然而已。
data.enText: Their early arrival was just an accident.
fortune

data.chText: 尤指影响人生的机会、运气：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) luck or chance, especially in the way it affects people's lives

data.chText: 只有那次我们运气好，那一天阳光普照。
data.enText: For once, fortune was on our side: the sun shone that day.
fate

data.chText: 指命运、天数、定数、天意：
data.enText: the power that is believed to control everything that happens and that cannot be stopped or changed

data.chText: 命中注定她永远到不了美国。
data.enText: Fate decreed that she would never reach America.
destiny

data.chText: 指主宰事物的力量、命运之神：
data.enText: the power that is believed to control events

data.chText: 我总认为有某种力量在指引着我们——叫它上帝也罢，天意也罢，还是命运也罢。
data.enText: I believe there's some force guiding us─call it God, destiny or fate.
providence

data.chText: 指上帝、苍天、天佑：
data.enText: ( formal ) God, or a force that some people believe controls our lives and the things that happen to us, usually in a way that protects us

data.chText: 他相信上苍。
data.enText: He trusted in divine providence.

data.chText: 用fate、destiny还是providence？
一般认为providence是善意的，即使降临苦难也是上帝安排的一部分；fate有时是善意的，但那只是意外的恩赐；同样经常地，fate也是残酷的，使人感到无能为力；destiny更可能给人力量的感觉，具有强烈使命感的人通常认为自己是天生伟大或成就伟大事业的人。
data.enText: Providence is usually seen as being kind: even when it sends suffering, this is accepted as being part of God's plan. Fate can be kind, but this is an unexpected gift; just as often, fate is cruel and makes people feel helpless. Destiny is more likely to give people a sense of power: people who have a strong sense of destiny usually believe that they are meant to be great or do great things.
fate, destiny or providence?
by/through …luck/chance/coincidence/accident
It was… luck/chance/coincidence/accident/fortune/fate/providence that…
It's no coincidence/accident that…
pure/sheer/mere luck/chance/coincidence/accident
good/bad/ill luck/fortune
to have the … luck/fortune to do sth
to tempt fate/providence (= to do sth too confidently in a way that might mean that your good luck will come to an end)
sb's luck/fortune changes/turns
a stroke of luck/fortune/fate
a twist of fortune/fate

means: 命中注定的事(尤指坏事)

ex.chText: 他们遭遇了同样的命运。
那个地区的穷人决不会接受被奴役的命运。
ex.enText: The poor people in the area will never accept the fate of slavery.

synonyms.bx: 多指不好的命运，带有不可避免的意味。

ex.chText: 有人告诉她嫁个有钱人是她的命。
ex.enText: She was told that it was her destiny to marry a rich man.

ex.chText: 他相信她来到这个城市是天意。
ex.enText: He believes that it is destiny that brings her to this city.

synonyms.bx: 指将来一定会发生在某人身上的事情，尤指无法改变或控制的事。

ex.chText: 数千居民在这场洪水中丧生。
ex.enText: Thousands of residents met their doom in this flood.

ex.chText: 整个国家都笼罩在厄运降临的气氛之中。
ex.enText: A sense of doom hung over the entire country.

synonyms.bx: 指不可避免的悲惨命运，如死亡、毁灭等。

ex.chText: 该组织许诺要改善穷人的处境。
ex.enText: The organization has promised to improve the lot of the poor.

ex.chText: 搬到这里以后，她似乎对自己的境况挺满意。
ex.enText: After moving here, she seemed to be satisfied with her lot.

synonyms.bx: 指工作、社会地位等所处的境况，尤指不太好的处境。

data.enText: to do sth too confidently in a way that might mean that your good luck will come to an end

tr: an event (or a course of events) that will inevitably happen in the future
the ultimate agency regarded as predetermining the course of events (often personified as a woman)
example: we are helpless in the face of destiny

tr: your overall circumstances or condition in life (including everything that happens to you)

example: She was destined to become a great pianist

value.def: Fate is a power that some people believe controls and decides everything that happens, in a way that cannot be prevented or changed. You can also refer to the fates .

example.ex: I see no use quarrelling with fate.
example.tran: 我看不出和命运抗争有什么用。

example.ex: It was just one of those times when you wonder whether the fates conspire against you.
example.tran: 有些时候，你会怀疑是不是造化弄人，现在就是如此。

value.def: A person's or thing's fate is what happens to them.

example.ex: The Russian Parliament will hold a special session later this month to decide his fate...
example.tran: 俄罗斯议会本月晚些时候将举行特别会议决定他的命运。

example.ex: He seems for a moment to be again holding the fate of the country in his hands...
example.tran: 他似乎在一瞬间又一次将国家的命运握在了手中。

example.ex: The Casino, where she had often danced, had suffered a similar fate.
example.tran: 她经常跳舞的赌场遭遇了相似的命运。

value.def: If something seals a person's or thing's fate, it makes it certain that they will fail or that something unpleasant will happen to them.

example.ex: The call for a boycott could be enough to seal the fate of next week's general election...
example.tran: 抵制选举的呼吁足以注定下周大选失败的命运。

example.ex: And yesterday the Zoo's fate was sealed, largely due to two months of ever-dwindling entrance figures.
example.tran: 昨日，伦敦动物园面临着关闭的命运，主要因为两个月来游客数量持续下滑。
